description:
This canyon is described in limited detail in Canyons Near Sydney by Rick Jamieson. Help the Australian canyoning community by contributing track notes to ropewiki.com

This was one of many well-known errors in Rick Jamieson's guidebook. The grid-reference is the lower section of Closet_(Newnes_Plateau). It's not known where the name "Tea-time Canyon" originated, although the next published canyon to the south is Breakfast Creek, so Breakfast and tea-time is a theme. Regardless, Jamieson's "Tea-time Canyon" is the lower section of Closet Canyon.
